<h2>What LG Dryer Calls in Dana Point Actually Look Like</h2>
<p>Dana Point's compact geography means almost every address gets meaningful coastal salt air — but the intensity varies by proximity to the harbour and bluffs.</p>

<p><strong>Dana Point Harbour area and Lantern District — maximum harbour exposure (92629).</strong> The residential streets immediately adjacent to the harbour basin and the Lantern District on Blue Lantern Street and Street of the Golden Lantern. These addresses get direct harbour salt air from the marina — boat traffic, salt water, constant marine breeze. Every gas dryer call from Harbour area and Lantern District gets full coastal protocol: flex connector inspection first regardless of stated problem, exterior vent cap damper test, marine-grade dielectric grease on every electrical connection. Connector corrosion in 2–3 years here. Lint plus harbour moisture creates a paste-like buildup in vent duct bends that is denser and harder to clear than standard dry-area lint — we use extended cleaning procedures on Lantern District calls where initial airflow measurement shows residual restriction after first pass. Persistent d80 after vent cleaning in the Lantern District is almost always a corroded cap damper — we replace rather than clean on harbour-adjacent caps.</p>

<p><strong>Capistrano Beach (Capo Beach) — southern Dana Point (92624).</strong> The beach community at the southern end of the city in ZIP 92624 — homes directly on the Pacific south of the harbour. Capo Beach has the most direct Pacific ocean exposure in Dana Point. Gas connector inspection on every Capo Beach call. Fine sand and coastal particulate enters exterior vent caps on beachfront Capo Beach properties — same pattern as Playa del Rey and Laguna Beach beachfront. The paste-like lint buildup from coastal humidity is most pronounced in Capo Beach's lowest-elevation beachfront homes. We replace caps and clear paste buildup on every Capo Beach call as standard procedure.</p>

<p><strong>Salt Creek Beach area — mid-coastal Dana Point (92629).</strong> The residential neighbourhoods around Salt Creek Beach between the harbour and Laguna Niguel border. Salt Creek sits at a middle coastal exposure level — more sheltered than the harbour and Capo Beach, more exposed than Dana Hills. Gas connector inspection standard. Vent cap check on every call. Homes backing onto the Salt Creek canyon corridor accumulate canyon debris in exterior caps faster than flat beachfront addresses — particularly during Santa Ana wind events in October through December.</p>

